"""
Convert between base 10 integers and a alphanumberic base using 4-Letter or 5-Letter common male and female first names
Name source is US Census data
3-Letter encoding uses selected names from ~970 most common names, with (some) problematic ones removed.
4-Letter encoding uses selected names from ~460 most common names, with (most) problematic ones removed.
    Filtered names are intended to be easier to recite if needed.
5-Letter encoding 1127 names with NO filtering.
Order of names have been randomized.
"""

